Black female executives continue to be the group that faces the most obstacles in ascending to the highest levels of corporate America. ⁣

Diversifying the boardroom is like “opening the windows and letting fresh air in the board room. We can’t think well with stale air”⁣
⁣
Corporate America continues to voice its commitment to increasing Black representation in the boardroom. We have assembled a group of speakers to review the state of specific initiatives to turn this stated mandate into institutional realities:⁣
⁣
Guy Primus: CEO and Board Member at Valence Enterprises⁣
@DBSoaries: Founder of dfree Financial Freedom Movement ⁣
Byron Loflin: Global Head of Board Engagement at @Nasdaq, ⁣
⁣
Head to Black Enterprise facebook to watch the full panel!

node.text:
Black executives continue to endlessly run on the corporate treadmill. In this session, our panelists discuss how corporations can structure intentional and effective programs to identify and groom Black professionals at each stage of their careers—a practice that is still all too common for white male professionals. Our panelists offer guidance to corporations on how to fix such inequities to position Blacks for key assignments and leadership positions. 

Head to diversity.blackenterprise.com or BE's social channels to catch the rest of the #DEIsummit!

node.title: What Corporate America Must Do to Advance Black Talent

In this session, we assemble a panel of CDOs to discuss their expansive roles in all areas of their corporation as a core driver of its business imperative. In a candid conversation, these corporate leaders discuss effective and transformative diversity, equity, and inclusion strategies and why they are required to meet the needs of employees, managers, customers, and other stakeholders now more than ever. 

Head to diversity.blackenterprise.com or BE's social channels to catch the rest of the #DEIsummit today!

node.text:
The Brooklyn native ventured into the coffee industry last year launching a specialty coffee brand called Coffee Uplifts People (CUP). Through research, she discovered that discriminatory practices have marginalized people of color in countries where coffee beans are harvested.⁠
⁠
Angela Yee and her two business partners, Tony Forte and LaRon Batchelor, created CUP to bring inclusiveness and diversity to every facet of the coffee business and supply chain. Not only have they created a coffee company with fair trade offerings, but CUP ultimately aims to shift the entire industry to become more equitable, especially for farmers of color.⁠
⁠
Link in bio for more!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Black Enterprise on July 28, 2021. May be an image of outdoors and text that says 'WALMART WILL BEGIN COVERING 100% OF COLLEGE TUITION AND BOOKS FOR ASSOCIATES Walmart'.

node.text:
Walmart’s part-time and full-time Walmart and Sam’s Club workers who are based in the U.S. can say farewell to student loan debt, according to a press release.⁠
⁠
All college tuition and books expenses will be covered for Walmart’s Live Better U (LBU) education program participants. Aug. 16 marks the big day that the perk will begin for associates. The current daily $1 fee will end for those who utilize LBU, to encourage a greater number of them to embark upon educational goals, according to Walmart’s announcement.⁠
⁠
Link in bio for more!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Black Enterprise on July 26, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'FACEBOOK IS OFFERING 100,000 SCHOLARSHIPS TO BLACK LEARNERS SEEKING DIGITAL MARKETING CERTIFICATIONS BLACK ENTERPRISE.COM'.

node.text:
The organization has launched an online application through the Facebook Elevate program to help more individuals gain access to industry-recognized career certifications. The social media behemoth is giving 100,000 scholarships to Black learners seeking gain access to vital digital skills. The scholarships can be used for the Facebook Certified Digital Marketing Associate Exam.⁠
⁠
Link in bio for more!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Black Enterprise on July 22, 2021. May be an image of 1 person, playing a sport and text that says 'SIMONE BILES BECOMES FIRST FEMALE ATHLETE WITH HER OWN TWITTER HASHTAG EMOJI'.

node.text:
Twitter has announced that it has created a custom hashtag emoji for the greatest gymnast of all time, Simone Biles. This achievement makes her the first female athlete and first Olympic athlete to get such acknowledgment on the Twitter platform.⁠
⁠
Link in bio for more!
